Feature: dalogin outbound HTTP client call observability

Contract IDs
- None (cross-cutting observability for existing internal service calls; no new client API contracts)

Overview
- Add structured logging and observability to all outbound HTTP calls from `dalogin-quarkus`
  to downstream services (`mbook-quarkus`, `mbooks-quarkus`).
- Cover both the request path (servlet → ServiceClient → downstream) and the response
  (status, body, latency, error).
- Follow the annotation-first pattern established in `speckit.system.backend-logging-observability`.

Role collaboration
- `@backend-dev`, `@security-specialist`, `@testing-engineer`, `@performance-engineer`

Call inventory
- `/login/CheckOut` GET  → `ServiceClient.clientToken()`  → `GET  /mbooks-1/rest/book/payment/clientToken`
- `/login/CheckOut` POST → `ServiceClient.checkOut()`     → `POST /mbooks-1/rest/book/payment/fullcheckout2`
- `/login/GetAllPurchases` GET → `ServiceClient.callGetPurchases()`  → `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/purchases`
- `/login/ManagePurchases` GET  → `ServiceClient.callGetTickets()`   → `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/purchases/tickets`
- `/login/ManagePurchases` POST → `ServiceClient.managePurchases()`  → `POST /mbooks-1/rest/book/managepurchases`
- `/login/ManagePurchases` POST → `ServiceClient.deletePurchases()`  → `POST /mbooks-1/rest/book/deletepurchases`
- (internal) `ServiceClient.callGetData()`   → `GET /mbook-1/rest/user/{user}/{token1}`
- (internal) `ServiceClient.callGetDevice()` → `GET /mbook-1/rest/device/{uuid}`

Key files
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/servlets/CheckOut.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/servlets/GetAllPurchases.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/servlets/ManagePurchases.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/client/ServiceClient.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/client/service/Purchases.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/client/service/User.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/client/service/Device.java`
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/java/com/dalogin/client/filter/RequestFilter.java`

Functional requirements
- `FR-001`: Every outbound call from `dalogin-quarkus` MUST emit a structured log on request dispatch.
- `FR-002`: Every call MUST emit a structured log on response received (status code, latency).
- `FR-003`: Failed calls (4xx, 5xx, exception) MUST emit an ERROR-level log with enough context to diagnose.
- `FR-004`: Logs MUST include: servlet source, ServiceClient method, downstream path, HTTP method, response status, latency.
- `FR-005`: `RequestFilter` header injection MUST be logged at DEBUG level (headers forwarded, Ciphertext fallback used).
- `FR-006`: Sensitive values (token2, Ciphertext, uuid, nonce) MUST be masked or omitted from logs.
- `FR-007`: Logs MUST be routed to a dedicated category/file separate from other log streams.

Log category
- `LOG-HTTP-CLIENT`: all outbound HTTP call events from dalogin to downstream services

Security requirements
- `SEC-001`: token2, Ciphertext, uuid, payment nonce MUST NOT appear in log messages.
- `SEC-002`: Cookie header values MUST NOT be logged verbatim; log cookie names only.
- `SEC-003`: RequestFilter DEBUG logs MUST log which headers were added, not their values.

Non-functional requirements
- `NFR-001`: Default log level INFO covers request dispatch + response summary.
- `NFR-002`: DEBUG covers RequestFilter header injection detail.
- `NFR-003`: Logging overhead MUST be negligible relative to HTTP round-trip time.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] All ServiceClient call methods produce structured START/END/ERROR log events.
- [ ] RequestFilter header injection is traceable at DEBUG level without leaking values.
- [ ] Sensitive fields are masked.
- [ ] Logs appear in the dedicated `LOG-HTTP-CLIENT` category/file.
- [ ] Both success and downstream error paths are covered.

Definition of Done
- [ ] Feature has spec, implementation, and tests.
- [ ] `@testing-engineer` verification done.
- [ ] `@security-specialist` verification done.
- [ ] `@performance-engineer` verification done.

